<document>
	<title>Studies on neutron activation analysis for the measurement of sodium
   in nails as a screening test for cystic fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Savory-J.</author>
	<author>Leitner-S-S.</author>

	<source>Ann-Clin-Lab-Sci. 1974 Nov-Dec. 4(6). P 413-9.</source>

	<abstract>The present study points out the simplicity and ease of using
   fingernails and toenails to measure electrolyte levels as a test
   for cystic fibrosis.  Procedures and various effects on the ranges
   of values for different categories of healthy and diseased subjects
   are discussed and the limitations of the method are indicated.</abstract>

